{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give temporary right to work for people subject to visa delays during COVID-19",
        "additional_details": "People could not leave the country to apply for visas due to COVID-19. \r\nHowever, they also can't leave the UK once the visa application has been made, as it makes it invalid.\r\nThe home office visa process normally takes 8 weeks, it has been delayed over 10 months for some.\r\nPeople are supporting families with new babies which were born in lockdown 1.\r\nOthers are NHS workers extending a visa, but being turned away from work.\r\nNot working for this long has an impact on people's mental health.",
        "background": "Grant the right to work for people who are subject to home office visa delays during the COVID-19 crisis. Allow people to seek employment on a temporary basis until the delays in the home office (which are over 10 months now) have stopped. Acknowledge the people in limbo who cannot leave or work.",
